ID:500491060_10152146142721061
Name:null
Story:N/A
Message:Here is a semi-complete (I say this because I'm positive there are other places) list of food establishments we must, as the youth profess, "hit up" during my time back in the States. While it is not necessary to exhaust this list I would like to "hit up" as many as possible so that I may look back upon this time and believe wholeheartedly that the 10 lbs I will inevitably gain from these adventures were, in fact, worth it. 

Watt's 
Merritt's 
La Farm 
Coquette 
BUFFALO WILD WINGS
Dame's 
Cafe Beyu (if only for a nostalgic drink)
Five Guys 
Med Deli
Founding Farmers (come to DC)
The lobstah truck (see above) 
Shiki (to kill this craving for American sushi)
Sugarland for a martini (nobody drives for three hours afterwards)
Lantern (for another nostalgic drink)
Irregardless Cafe 
Allen & Sons 

Please add to this list as you see fit. Upon hitting the tender age of 23 I can no longer ingest caffeine without disastrous side effects and I am sure that even the capabilities of my memory have been affected by the epidemic of "old age." 

Sayoko Sueyoshi

Name:Israel, Gaza, War & Data
Story:N/A
Message:By far the best article I've seen on how the traditional media and social media color our perception of the situation in Gaza. A must-read.

"If you?re rooting for Israel, you might have seen videos of rocket launches by Hamas adjacent to Shifa Hospital. Alternatively, if you?re pro-Palestinian, you might have seen the following report on an alleged IDF sniper who admitted (on Instagram) to murdering 13 Gazan children. Israelis and their proponents are likely to see IDF videos such as this one detailing arms and tunnels found within mosques passed around in their social media feeds, while Palestinian groups are likely to pass around images displaying the sheer destruction caused by IDF forces to Gazan mosques. One side sees videos of rockets intercepted in the Tel-Aviv skies, and other sees the lethal aftermath of a missile attack on a Gazan neighborhood."

Ziyou, you should do the "Detailed Module Descriptions" section for the Design Document. If it doesn't, though, you could just list our main modules (UI, Grapes, Renderer, etc.) and the parameters they take.

Turner, is there anything else on the website that needs to get done? User Manual, or something? I can work on that too.

ID:646885269_588396221244102
Name:How to drive object attributes in Maya with music-sound (Tutorial)
Story:N/A
Message:I think we should all watch this video asap.

Our work may be partially cut out for us. Of course, we could always work to make the visualization more pretty or awesome (grapes). But it looks like this might take care of the foundations once and for all.

Incidentally, the "audiowave" node's only output-modifying attribute is "Scale". It looks like this is just a simple output scaling factor. Ideally, though, we'd have a full DFT breakdown, and we could control output not just by modifying scale, but also by restricting the amplitude readout to particular bands of frequency, etc. Ideally, we could select bands and then output a single scaled amplitude readout for each of these bands.

Anyway, though, this is a big deal. That would be awesome if we could get the audiowave source code, though I doubt it.

Message:International outlook 

 Our portfolio is looking to avoid the Japanese economy as the latest quarter GDP results reveal the anaemic growth that the country is experiencing. We are doubtful that the stimulus package the Bank of Japan is administering will yield much result as companies are holding onto low inventory levels. Similarly the Australian economy is looking stagnant with no new information being reported by the Reserve Bank of Australia. The Aussie saw a peculiar increase than immediate decrease of from 93 US cents to 92.69 by statements released to the public. As the Australian economy seems uncertain with its direction our portfolio is also to avoid this sector.

Story:Joo Oh Park added 26 photos.
Message:So this Japanese mofo (Shinnosuke Koyanagi) visited Korea with absolutely no plan...messaging me the very first day saying he couldnt get in the hostel he booked thats a galaxy away from the city center...Please research before you travel anywhere.

His three day trip to Korea consisted of plethora of local Korean experiences...such as sleeping in a love motel (with me), eating raw beef, liver, stomach, Korean barbeque and "four seasons soup" (you don't wanna know), drinking in Gangnam and Itaewon and sightseeing at Hooker Hill (trust me... only sightseeing)... things that you could never get with package tour with your parents.

It was great to see an old friend who spent the time of your life together in our young age. Its also amazing how little we changed...that's brotherhood, man. Now I am looking forward to visiting this dude im the close future.

Cheers bro, thanks for visiting. Also thanks ??? (Hank) who responded faster than anyone and did not hesitate to share the moment with us.

ID:687379038_596353867115004
Name:null
Story:N/A
Message:Hey so what I think I'm going to do for my portion is expect as input 3 integers that sum to 32 (they will be bass, mid-range, treble passed in that order) so I'll figure out how to aggregate the ranges.  Then I'll expect an int (1,2, or 3 indicating bass, mid, treble to control color of the object).  Lastly I'll take two parameters (may be 1,2, or 3) to control the size, second to control x-y distortion.
I'm planning on having a bunch of ellipses that will have variable size, color, and semi-major to major axis ratio.  So the call to my function will be ellipseScene(int bass, int mid, int treble, int color, int size, int ratio).  Note that the last three inputs may have the same value or all different.
Let me know if you guys have any questions for implementing the ui/test cases for my portion.

ID:687379038_577648442318880
Name:null
Story:N/A
Message:I think I'm going to email stotts this tomorrow and say that these are the requirements/use cases we came up with.  If any of you have anything to add or change let me know.  Also, I said mov file since maya doesn't have an avi file format for rendering in mac for some reason. If one of the windows people can let me know if the mov file format is available in windows that would be great.  I also think the 72 hours thing is not going to happen from what I can tell it takes forever to render videos.

Requirements

Tier 1:
 The plugin must run in Maya versions 2014 and 2013.
 The plugin must allow a user to choose an mp3 file to use as the audio source.
 The plugin must produce a video with format mov the Quicktime format.
 The plugin must present a GUI for the user to choose mp3 file as well as save  location for the mov file.

Tier 2:
 The plugin must allow for a user to choose different ?classes? of animation, such  as a group of spheres, a plane of water, or a single ?spiky? sphere.
 The plugin must allow for the user to view a ?rough? rendering of the video in the  viewport in real time.

Tier 3:
 The plugin must allow for the user to choose which audio aspects control certain  visual properties.
 The plugin must allow for different strengths of audio aspects to contribute to  its corresponding visual property.
 The plugin must render a final video in 72 hours time.

Use Cases:

As a user, I want to be able to choose which song to play and have coupled with visualization.

As a user I want to be able to choose which type of visualization is shown.

As a user I want a final video file to be produced once parameters are chosen and decided to be rendered.

As a user I want to be able to see a "rough demo" within the viewport in real time.

As a user I want to be able to decide which audio properties control which visualization properties.

Message:Thanks for the verse nomination, Irene Li<3

 Two people working together will produce greater results for their labor: if one should fall, the other is there to help his fellow-worker up. Nevertheless, if one should fall who tries to stand alone, no one will be there to help him back up, and thus he will suffer loss. To put it another way, if two lie together they will keep warm; but how could anyone keep warm while lying alone? Or, if one were to stand alone in battle, another could overpower him; but if two people were to standing together, they could withstand an attack; and three people would be even better, because a threefold cord is not easily broken! (Ecclesiastes 4:9-12)

For I know the plans I have for you, declares the LORD, plans for welfare and not for evil, to give you a future and a hope. (Jeremiah 29:11 )

Name:Support ALS research! Ice bucket challenge
Story:N/A
Message:The purpose of this video is to raise awareness and raise funding for ALS (I did not pour ice water over myself for no reason!), which is a neurodegenerative disease with no cure as of today.  This disease destroys the communication pathway from brain to muscular tissue.  
Thank you Diana Kao and UNC Lambda Upsilon Lambda for nominating me to this Challenge. Also, thanks to Vanessa Pang for filming the video.  This ice bucket challenge has raised over 2.9 billion dollars all over the nation for research to find a cure for ALS (sorry i said the amount wrong in the video). Yayyyy~! 

You can make a donation easily at alsa.org/donate :D

Next, I would like to nominate Kyle Ri, Joseph Luan, Sarah Heywood, Michelle Kanon, and Ncsu Kappas to this challenge!

 spread the word and help fight~ <3

Message:Tagged by my and my only nerdy partner in crime Angelina Eimannsberger

1. She, Maire Jaanus 
2. The Archeology of Mind, Jaak Panksepp 
3. Once a Dancer, Allegra Kent (and all sorts of biographies) 
4. The Representations of Intellectual, Edward Said 
5. My Sister's Keeper, Jodi Picoult (I cried my heart out in the end; I was 14 year old) 
6. Social Intelligence, Daniel Goleman 
7. My name is Red, Orhan Pamuk (As a high schooler, I did not understand it at all, and somehow this sense of strangeness has stuck in my mind ever since) 
8. Protagoras, Plato 
9. Uncountable fairytales & children's stories
10. Le files, Michel Rostain (I have not yet read it; somehow I kept this one after leaving almost all my read and unread books behind when I moved to my forth apartment this year) 
11. AND OH, how can I not include my complete DVD collection of Friends? ;)

"List 10 books that have stayed with you in some way. Don't take more than a few minutes and don't think too hard - they don't have to be the "right" or "great" works, just the ones that have touched you. Tag 10 friends (or as many as you think would be interested to play) including me, so I'll see your list."

ID:1411980942_758170544193937
Name:null
Story:N/A
Message:Hola! Here's the basic HatCH schedule for February:

2/6: Planning/Artisan Pizza Kitchen @ 7:30, HatCH
2/13: CANCELED
2/20: Quadcopter Night w/ MORE PIZZA @ 7:30, HatCH
2/27: jQuery/Bootstrap Fest w/ prizes @ 7:30, HatCH

And here's a breakdown of this month: 
1) During our first meeting we'll head out to Artisan Pizza Kitchen for a brainstorming session about how we can move HatCH forward as a group and make it more interactive/fun for all members. I'll also be talking about how we'll structure leadership next year after I graduate. 
2) Our second meeting will be EARLY as we will be heading out to see Lile Stephen's Operating System exhibition. Lile is a friend of HatCH and this will be an awesome opportunity to see how art and technology can converge. 
3) It's time we actually work on that quadcopter so we can start our world pizza delivery business :D. We'll need to gather whatever supplies we need for real this time, and get started on this thing. To celebrate (and to keep an eye on the competition) I'll also order pizza for everyone!
4) Finally, we're going to try to have an easy coding event during the last meeting of the month. We'll all meet in HatCH and learn the jQuery/Bootstrap frameworks, with a goal to make simple apps. If we're productive we could even set new members up with Github accounts and post them up there. Top three hacks will get (silly) prizes. This will be a great warmup for HackNC too, which you should sign up for if you haven't already!
ID:1411980942_757383880939270
Name:null
Story:N/A
Message:After discussion, it has been decided that HatCH will become a more active organization which will allow us to practice programming in a structured way while also fostering more of a sense of community through various events every month.

I'll be planning something along these lines for each month:
-Software hack night (food, friendly competition, (silly) prizes)
-Social event (dinner, mini-tech talk, etc.)
-Hardware hack (killer robots, pizza delivery quadcopters, etc.)

If anyone has any suggestions please let me know, I'll provide details for this month within the next week :D

tl;dr we're going to do stuff now so bring your robot parts to class

ID:1531609000_10201669923259817
Name:null
Story:N/A
Message:Today i walked into Teague and saw all the empty rooms and halls. I felt empty. Today was graduation. It's suppose to be a happy day, but somehow i felt sad.   I walked out of the global center after the econ commencement in a hurry without really saying good byes to my friends because i was tired. I didnt realize that this is one of the last few moments we will have together. In a couple of days, we would all depart. Although we all say "keep in touch" and "visit each other often", the ugly truth is that we probably wont. Its not that we dont value our friendship. Its that we are now going into the real world to start our new life and family, and itll be hard to sit back, relax, and reconnect with our old friends from our busy lives.  Throughout these four years, i made some great friends; some with annoying qualities haha. But today, when its time to depart, all i see and remember are the good times we had together, because thats wut really matters.  This last senior year has been crazy. I had so much fun! Thanks guys for a great year! These are the best times i had on college. I really hope that these days can last forever where we just drink and play random games. Thanks guys! Im not gonna wish u guys good luck for ur post graduation lives because i know you guys wont need it. Im gonna wish for us to be able to come back and relive our days together soon! <3

Message:Thanks Lekha for what I'll call the "Book Challenge" nomination. Here are my 10 books:
1. Flow: The Psychology of Optimal Experience -Mihaly Csikszentmihalyi
2. My Brother Sam is Dead - James and Lincoln Collier
3. Ender's Game - Orson Scott Card
4. Leading with the Heart - Mike Krzyzewski
5. 1776 - David McCullough
6. On the Sweet Spot: Stalking the Effortless Present - Richard Keefe
7. A Short History of Nearly Everything - Bill Bryson
8. Narrative of the Life of Frederick Douglass - F.D.
9. Iran Awakening - Shirin Ebadi
10. On China - Henry Kissinger

The rules: "In your status, list 10 books that have stayed with you in some way. Don't take more than a few minutes and don't think too hard - they don't have to be the "right" books or great works of literature, just ones that have affected you in some way. I challenge Emmanuel, Federico, Mark, Martin, Kaighn, Justin, Will, Chang, David, James. Have fun!

Story:N/A
Message:ESPN rates Coach K No. 4 best men's college basketball coach in recent years. Here are some interesting stats: Since 2006-07, Duke has won just 1 regular season ACC title. In 6 of those 8 seasons, Duke failed to progress past the Sweet 16. In 3 of those 6 seasons, they lost their 1st NCAA tournament game. In 2 of the last 3 years, they've been sent home right away, by a No. 15 and No. 14 seed, respectively. But, from Nov. 26, 2007, to Jan. 6, 2014, Duke never once ranked outside the Associated Press top 10. The Blue Devils spent 122 straight weeks without falling below No.10, the longest streak since Wooden's UCLA Bruins from 1966-1976. They won it all in 2010. Those stats epitomize Duke in my recent memory.

Message:IWS & IWR (US Russell Mid-Cap Value) - Buy
We decided to continue hold IWS as part of our long-term strategy. We believe investors will seek these equities once the market pullback stops. We made these trades as a contrarian play for above average return. Even with the murky job reports, consumer services are improving with the report two weeks ago and recent news, making US equities attractive.

EEM, ACWI, EWG, & IOO (Emerging Markets) - Buy
We decided to buy emerging markets due to their heavier weight on tech and financial services aboard. These sectors have done well lately as investors are beginning to stray away from US equity and more into foreign investments.

Name:null
Story:N/A
Message:Macro-economic Outlook
Domestic and International

For this week, the economic calendar reports on S&P Case-Shiller HPI, New Home Sales, Consumer Confidence, Durable Goods Orders, Pending Home Sales Index, Consumer Sentiment, Personal Income and Outlays, and GDP.

Although equities ended on a positive note last week, our team evaluated our current holdings and closed the positions that looked susceptible to increasing volatility and swings within the markets.  Today, we entered new positions that were more conservative and protected against heavy losses. These positions have significantly limited the downturn that is happening in equities.  

Although we have a positive outlook for the economy, most investors are overreacting, and their fears are driving momentum towards these ups and downs.  Our team believes that the economy is improving and the economic indicators show it.  Therefore, we have temporarily entered positions in alternative investments, emerging market investments, long-term bonds, and midcap value stocks.  Equities will improve once positive numbers on GDP and other indicators come out this week.  Then, we will re-apply an aggressive allocation investment strategy as soon as investors begin to realize that they were wrong about their economic outlook.  

The Ukraine crisis, FOMC announcement, and China?s problems have caused uncertainty regarding the recovery.  As the Russian economy continues to be downgraded as an emerging market, foreign investment will focus on frontier markets instead of BRIC countries and limit exposure to the Ukraine Crisis and Putin's legacy, such as the annexation of Crimea and announcement of suspending Russia from the G-7 summit.

Message:Happy 21st Birthday to the best campaign manager ever, Zach Bijesse! When the Carolina Review asked me earlier this year this question: What is the one thing about Carolina that you love most? My answer was: "I would have to say the students. I?ll tell you a story. So my first few days on campus, (I come from a very small town) I was overwhelmed the first few days and I didn?t know that many people. So I ate alone a lot during the first few weeks. One day I was sitting down for lunch at Rams and across from me there is another student. As I sat down, the person across from me asked if I wanted to sit with him. I said ok (after being apprehensive), but at the time, I didn?t think much of it, kind of like I would never see him again. A few weeks later, I saw him again and we just sat together.  Three years later, he is one of my best friends and he is my campaign manager." One of my favorite Carolina memories!

Message:THANKS FOR COMING TO DUMPLING NIGHT!!! :) And shout out to the best dumpling chef, Qianli Wang, and CJ Yoon,  Chuner Guo, Dalen Kuang, Christopher Mejias, Brooke Liang, and Phuong for doing a ton of work prepping and cleaning. Hope you guys had as much fun as I did!! 

For anyone who was asking for the recipe, here's a list of ingredients (sorry we're not very good at measurements): 

Dough: flour, water, salt (optional) 

Pork filling: ground pork, egg, cabbage (chop really small, then squeeze water out), green onion, cilantro, soy sauce, sesame oil, vegetable oil, pepper, salt 

Veggie filling: shiitake mushrooms, carrots, cabbage, green onion, soy sauce, sesame oil, pepper, salt

ID:100001043113693_771080102936753
Name:null
Story:N/A
Message:Today i walked into Teague and saw all the empty rooms and halls. I felt empty. Today was graduation. It's suppose to be a happy day, but somehow i felt sad.   I walked out of the global center after the econ commencement in a hurry without really saying good byes to my friends because i was tired. I didnt realize that this is one of the last few moments we will have together. In a couple of days, we would all depart. Although we all say "keep in touch" and "visit each other often", the ugly truth is that we probably wont. Its not that we dont value our friendship. Its that we are now going into the real world to start our new life and family, and itll be hard to sit back, relax, and reconnect with our old friends from our busy lives.  Throughout these four years, i made some great friends; some with annoying qualities haha. But today, when its time to depart, all i see and remember are the good times we had together, because thats wut really matters.  This last senior year has been crazy. I had so much fun! Thanks guys for a great year! These are the best times i had on college. I really hope that these days can last forever where we just drink and play random games. Thanks guys! Im not gonna wish u guys good luck for ur post graduation lives because i know you guys wont need it. Im gonna wish for us to be able to come back and relive our days together soon! <3

Message:Sales & Marketing High School Representatives (Now Accepting Applications!)

To those who are now studying at U.S. high schools:
Are you interested in real-world business? Do you want to show your leadership skills through meaningful extracurricular experiences? Are you seeking ways to make a real impact on your community? Do you want to join a company run by top U.S. college students and earn management positions in your college years?

Then join us! We partner with Findingschool.net and have established the ?Finding Your Leaper Program?. As a Sales & Marketing Representative at the U.S. high schools, you would collaborate with top U.S. college students to carry out marketing plans, improve our services and gain first-hand exposure to the business world. 

Benefits:
1. Great resume boost for college application
2. Networking opportunities with college students from Harvard, Princeton, UPenn, Duke and many more!
3. Opportunities to show your leadership, marketing and business skills
4. A possibility to take management-level positions in college years
5. Rewards available from sales

Requirements:
1. A junior or senior in a U.S. high school
2. Outstanding performance in academic and extracurricular activities
3. Great communication skills
4. Responsible and able to meet time commitment (1-3 hours/week)
5. Ability to effectively reach out to targeted student populations

Responsibilities:
1. Design and execute a local marketing strategy with the goal of growing awareness and participation in Leap
2. Develop original content, including videos, stories, posters, and other multimedia assets to promote Leap
3. Other job duties as assigned

Deadline?January 25th?2013

How to apply?
Please write a short essay (less than 250 words) about why you want to join Leap and how you would contribute to our program. Please email your essay and your most recent academic transcript to leap.program.usa@gmail.com

After receiving your application, we will conduct phone interviews to qualified candidates. We would accept candidates on a rolling basis. Since the spots fill up quickly, please apply as soon as possible. The last day to apply is January 25th, 2013, but we are very likely to close our admission before then.

Please check more relevant information at: www.leap-usa.com
We are looking forward to speaking with you about your interests!



Leap Consulting Co.Ltd.
A Peer Mentor Program for International Students at U.S. High Schools
www.leap-usa.com
leap.program.usa@gmail.com

ID:100002209942621_622660121150980
Name:null
Story:N/A
Message:Today i walked into Teague and saw all the empty rooms and halls. I felt empty. Today was graduation. It's suppose to be a happy day, but somehow i felt sad.   I walked out of the global center after the econ commencement in a hurry without really saying good byes to my friends because i was tired. I didnt realize that this is one of the last few moments we will have together. In a couple of days, we would all depart. Although we all say "keep in touch" and "visit each other often", the ugly truth is that we probably wont. Its not that we dont value our friendship. Its that we are now going into the real world to start our new life and family, and itll be hard to sit back, relax, and reconnect with our old friends from our busy lives.  Throughout these four years, i made some great friends; some with annoying qualities haha. But today, when its time to depart, all i see and remember are the good times we had together, because thats wut really matters.  This last senior year has been crazy. I had so much fun! Thanks guys for a great year! These are the best times i had on college. I really hope that these days can last forever where we just drink and play random games. Thanks guys! Im not gonna wish u guys good luck for ur post graduation lives because i know you guys wont need it. Im gonna wish for us to be able to come back and relive our days together soon! <3

ID:100002813248009_454019568035147
Name:null
Story:N/A
Message:Today i walked into Teague and saw all the empty rooms and halls. I felt empty. Today was graduation. It's suppose to be a happy day, but somehow i felt sad.   I walked out of the global center after the econ commencement in a hurry without really saying good byes to my friends because i was tired. I didnt realize that this is one of the last few moments we will have together. In a couple of days, we would all depart. Although we all say "keep in touch" and "visit each other often", the ugly truth is that we probably wont. Its not that we dont value our friendship. Its that we are now going into the real world to start our new life and family, and itll be hard to sit back, relax, and reconnect with our old friends from our busy lives.  Throughout these four years, i made some great friends; some with annoying qualities haha. But today, when its time to depart, all i see and remember are the good times we had together, because thats wut really matters.  This last senior year has been crazy. I had so much fun! Thanks guys for a great year! These are the best times i had on college. I really hope that these days can last forever where we just drink and play random games. Thanks guys! Im not gonna wish u guys good luck for ur post graduation lives because i know you guys wont need it. Im gonna wish for us to be able to come back and relive our days together soon! <3

Message:This afternoon, I received a call and then an email from MIT, officially notifying me that I have been admitted to the Ph.D. program in Chemical Engineering at MIT. Right now, I feel elated, euphoric, enraptured, excited, and enchanted. I am really looking forward to what is coming for me!
I am making this Facebook post in order to share the great news with all my friends who have been constantly caring for me. I would also like to thank all those who have given me support during the past few years, and particularly while I was preparing the applications. Special acknowledgement goes to my flatmates (Zak Holdaway, Jimmy Liu, and Kori Sutton) in 2013 ? these guys offered me direct, useful, and unparalleled assistance for my applications and also did all the dishes. The ChemMat Class of Awesome '13 and all the staff in the department are also to be thanked for giving me such a memorable experience as an undergraduate at the University of Auckland.
I am going tag those who have asked about the results of my Ph.D. applications, but my gratitude goes to all. I am tagging: Christopher, Kirsty, Carlos, Harry, Vamsi, David, Queenie, Daniel, Darren, Benjamin, Ashvin, Aksiniya, Brush, Etern, Ryan, Paul, Echo, and Lily.

Name:Ohio lawmakers want to limit the teaching of the scientific process
Story:N/A
Message:From wikipedia: "The scientific method is a way to ask and answer scientific questions by making observations and doing experiments.
The steps of the scientific method are to:
1) Ask a Question
2) Do Background Research
3) Construct a Hypothesis
4) Test Your Hypothesis by Doing an Experiment
5) Analyze Your Data and Draw a Conclusion
6) Communicate Your Results"

Ohio representatives think this method of thinking should be banned. Ask yourself 'why?', and please, if you live in the state of Ohio, contact them. If you are a person of faith, consider the possibility of a positive God who would never want us to raise children who are close minded and not curious about the world he/she created. Either way, this is important.

Message:Alright, guys. This weekend we should all get some serious work done. This is basically our last weekend to work on our scene. I'm working pretty hard, and creating some legit visualization stuff. Next week, we can start combining our features.

James, you should really try to get the rendering stuff working. There HAS TO be a way in Maya to output a video. This is Maya. There's no way they don't have capabilities for this stuff.

Ziyou, you should do the "Detailed Module Descriptions" section for the Design Document. I already wrote a bunch of stuff there, but apparently he wants us to use a formal documentation generator, like javadoc. I don't know if such a thing exists for MEL. If it doesn't, though, you could just list our main modules (UI, Grapes, Renderer, etc.) and the parameters they take.

Turner, is there anything else on the website that needs to get done? User Manual, or something? I can work on that too.

ID:100003507133980_573910066026051
Name:null
Story:N/A
Message:Hey guys sorry I missed the meeting today. I talked to Ben about it earlier but yeah I'm an idiot and I overslept. I've been thinking about new project ideas today. This is the idea I've come up with:

Write a plug in for Maya that enables the user to animate scenes based on an audio source. Maya is the industry standard 3D rendering program and it doesn't support anything like this. There is already a similar feature called SoundEffector in a different program, Cinema4D. This video shows what I'm talking about:

http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LSKIGgTRxtk

The song sucks but it looks really cool. Our demos would kick the shit out of everybody elses.

Maya offers free educational licenses to people like us and uses a plug-in architecture, so it is possible to extend the software. Their development platform supports creating new plugins with Python, MEL, and C++. In addition we would be able to use a lot of built in features in order to get our end result. Maya already allows you to import audio files and has loads of animation options. So this plugin would be a good size for the remainder of the semester.

Here is a link to what Maya is:

http://www.autodesk.com/products/autodesk-maya/overview

 Let me know what you guys think.

Message:This month of February, Carolina China Network is excited to present a discussion entitled China & Africa: Define the Relationship on Friday, February 28th from 4-5pm in Union Room 3206.  We are keen on exposing students on our campus to the myriad of reasons why China has turned attention to Africa?s continent and what opportunities and consequences have come about.  The short one-hour event will be a great chance to come together and eat free Chinese dumplings and discuss economic, diplomatic, and cultural collaborations from a high-level viewpoint.  Our goal is for each person in the room to hear, share, and learn something new about the Sino-Africa relationship that they may not have heard or considered before, and to meet someone in the room that you could continue the conversation with beyond this event!

    ???????????????? ???????????????? ??????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????

 

 

    Jim Morgan  was named  President  and CEO  of Krispy  Kreme Doughnuts, Inc. in January 2008. Mr. Morgan has been a member of the Krispy  Kreme  Board  of Directors  since  2000  and was elected its Chairman in 2005.

 

    Mr. Morgan served as Chairman and CEO of Wachovia Securities following the acquisition of Interstate/Johnson Lane, Inc. (IJL) by Wachovia  Corporation.   He  also  served  as Chairman  and  CEO of Interstate/Johnson Lane, Inc.. Mr. Morgan is a past member of the Securities Industry Association Board of Directors and the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) regional firms committee, and is currently on the Board of Directors of Coca-Coca Bottling Company Consolidated. Mr. Morgan has more than 40 years of business experience and is a

1969 graduate of Vanderbilt University. He also served as a lieutenant in the U.S. Navy.
